      <hedline>
        <hl1>2 Music Critics Get New Roles</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York Times names Bernard Holland to new post of national music critic; names Anthony Tommasini to succeed him as chief music critic (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bernard Holland, who has been the chief music critic of The New York Times for five years, has been named to the new position of national music critic.</p>
        <p>In that capacity he will review major concerts across the country, said John Darnton, the paper's culture editor, who made the announcement yesterday.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Bernard Holland, who has been the chief music critic of The New York Times for five years, has been named to the new position of national music critic.</p>
        <p>In that capacity he will review major concerts across the country, said John Darnton, the paper's culture editor, who made the announcement yesterday.</p>
        <p>Anthony Tommasini, a music reviewer for the paper, will succeed Mr. Holland as chief critic.</p>
      </block>
